02:11.390 --> 02:14.850
Hey, Dad. Now that I'm probably
gonna be the family wizard,

02:14.890 --> 02:16.820
I think it's time I get
that family wizard robe

02:16.860 --> 02:19.060
everyone's always talking about.

02:19.090 --> 02:22.560
- Is, uh... Is this it?
- Get out of there.

02:22.600 --> 02:25.230
No! The family wizard robe

02:25.270 --> 02:27.330
is a symbol of power and status

02:27.370 --> 02:29.270
that's handed down through the generations

02:29.300 --> 02:31.200
to the next family wizard.

02:31.240 --> 02:34.410
Now, I understood some
of the words you just said.

02:34.440 --> 02:36.910
And it still makes me think I
should be the one in our family

02:36.940 --> 02:40.050
- to have that robe.
- Yeah, well, I...

02:40.080 --> 02:42.950
I sort of gave it to Justin
when he was in the lead.

02:42.980 --> 02:45.820
I understood all of
the words you just said,

02:45.850 --> 02:47.120
and I did not like them.

02:48.750 --> 02:51.650
Dad, are you kidding me?
I deserve that robe.

02:51.690 --> 02:53.460
Yeah...
Yes, you do.

02:53.490 --> 02:56.290
But it's really special to Justin.

02:56.330 --> 02:58.730
It's gonna be very tough
to get it from him.

02:58.760 --> 03:03.370
We're gonna have to dance
delicately around this subject.

03:03.400 --> 03:05.400
Dance delicately.

03:05.440 --> 03:07.440
You mean like this?

03:13.210 --> 03:15.150
I don't know how this is gonna
help us get the robe back,

03:15.180 --> 03:17.250
but it sure is fun.

03:19.150 --> 03:21.090
Knock it off!

03:24.090 --> 03:26.690
OK. We gotta butter him up.

03:26.730 --> 03:28.430
Like corn?

03:29.630 --> 03:30.630
Just follow my lead.

03:30.670 --> 03:34.230
Hey, hey, hey!
How you doin'?

03:34.270 --> 03:36.300
There he is!
My favorite son!

03:36.340 --> 03:38.940
Wow. You look
really cool today.

03:38.970 --> 03:41.610
Did you do something new to your hair?

03:41.640 --> 03:43.850
No, I just carefully
messed it up with some hair gel

03:43.880 --> 03:46.180
to make it look, you know,
casually messed up.

03:46.220 --> 03:48.350
Man, that's cool!

03:48.380 --> 03:51.620
That is really, really cool.

03:51.650 --> 03:54.020
You know what else
is cool about you, Justin?

03:54.060 --> 03:56.490
You don't get
super-attached to things.

03:56.530 --> 03:59.260
That is true, I don't get
super-attached to things.

03:59.300 --> 04:02.130
You know, I'm a simple man
of concepts and ideas.

04:02.160 --> 04:04.930
Great.
Here's an idea.

04:04.970 --> 04:08.540
How about we give my second favorite son,

04:08.570 --> 04:11.610
- the family robe.
- What?

04:11.640 --> 04:14.640
- You gave it to me.
- Dad, is this the part

04:14.680 --> 04:16.209
where I start dancing delicately?

04:20.649 --> 04:22.720
I know I gave it to you, Justin,

04:22.750 --> 04:24.820
but that was before you disgraced yourself

04:24.860 --> 04:27.120
by revealing that you were
a wizard and all that.

04:27.160 --> 04:30.760
Disgraced myself?

04:30.800 --> 04:33.630
Are you even lookin' at him?

04:38.370 --> 04:41.300
No, I'm sorry, I'm not
gonna give him the robe.

04:41.340 --> 04:44.310
I haven't lost this competition
yet, and I'm not planning to.

04:44.340 --> 04:45.980
This is my moment,

04:46.010 --> 04:47.450
when I can rise from the ashes of defeat

04:47.480 --> 04:50.880
and take my rightful place
as the Russo family wizard.

04:50.920 --> 04:52.680
- But Justin...
- And you know something?

04:52.720 --> 04:55.850
Yes, I do get
super-attached to things!

05:01.790 --> 05:04.700
Well, that didn't go so well.

05:04.730 --> 05:07.830
And I'm sorry I said he was my favorite.

05:07.870 --> 05:09.200
Don't worry about it, Dad.

05:09.240 --> 05:11.540
To be honest, I've always preferred Mom.

05:19.350 --> 05:20.750
Land sakes, woman!

05:20.780 --> 05:24.220
You're all over the road like a
pat of butter on a hot skillet!

05:24.250 --> 05:25.850
Please don't yell at me,
Mr. Laritate.

05:25.890 --> 05:27.750
It only makes me drive worse.

05:27.790 --> 05:30.160
Teaching Driver's Ed
is not worth the overtime pay.

05:31.890 --> 05:36.430
I'm never gonna be able to afford
matching cowhide seat covers.

05:38.160 --> 05:39.870
Stay between the white lines, Harper.

05:39.900 --> 05:41.130
Oh, right.

05:44.070 --> 05:48.110
- Watch your speed.
- Thanks.

05:48.140 --> 05:51.310
Bus pulling out.

05:51.340 --> 05:56.450
- Sorry!
- All right, that's it.

05:56.480 --> 05:59.420
Make a left and pull over in front
of that restaurant over there.

05:59.450 --> 06:02.760
I need to get something healthy
to eat to calm my nerves.

06:02.790 --> 06:05.760
But, that's a donut shop.

06:07.600 --> 06:10.430
Then I'll get the ones with fruit inside.

06:13.370 --> 06:15.670
Well, we survived.

06:15.700 --> 06:20.110
We can all thank my lucky
life-saving hula girl.

06:20.140 --> 06:22.280
You're next, Alex.

06:22.310 --> 06:23.910
Come on, Leilani.

06:23.950 --> 06:26.350
You deserve one with coconut sprinkles.

06:32.390 --> 06:34.590
Hey, Alex, thanks for the driving tips.

06:34.620 --> 06:35.890
I think they actually helped me.

06:35.930 --> 06:36.890
- Really?
- Yeah.

06:36.930 --> 06:38.060
That's great, Harper.

06:40.400 --> 06:43.270
Guess I can do some things without magic.

06:43.300 --> 06:45.270
Just because I've used magic as a shortcut

06:45.300 --> 06:46.640
for as long as I can remember.

06:46.670 --> 06:48.870
- Um, Alex...
- Doesn't mean I can't live

06:48.910 --> 06:50.570
a very successful, ordinary life.

06:52.610 --> 06:55.480
We just crashed the car, didn't we?

06:55.510 --> 06:58.550
- We?
- I had to try.

